  34: <head>
  35: <title>OGNL Overview</title>
  36: <body>
  37:     <p>OGNL stands for Object-Graph Navigation Language; it is an expression language
  38:     for getting and setting properties of Java objects. You use the same expression
  39:     for both getting and setting the value of a property.</p>
  40: 
  41:     <p>OGNL started out as a way to set up associations between UI
  42:     components and controllers using property names.  As the desire for
  43:     more complicated associations grew, Drew Davidson created what he
  44:     called KVCL, for Key-Value Coding Language, egged on by Luke
  45:     Blanshard.  Luke then reimplemented the language using ANTLR, came up
  46:     with the new name, and, egged on by Drew, filled it out to its current
  47:     state.</p>
  48: 
  49:     <p>We pronounce OGNL as a word, like the last syllables of a drunken
  50:     pronunciation of "orthogonal" or like "ogg-null".</p>
  51: </body>
  52: </html>
